Hi guys, I'm having a bit of trouble with the PHP client api. I'm trying to do a search on deals but when I try to run my program, I get an SSL Certificate issue:
```Exception when calling search_api->do_search: [0] cURL error 60: SSL certificate problem: unable to get local issuer certificate (see https:/
/curl.haxx.se/libcurl/c/libcurl-errors.html) for <https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v3/objects/deals/search>```
I'm like 90% sure I've just misconfigured something and wanted to see if anyone could provide some insight. I used the basic code from the HubSpot docs:
```<?php
// requires and uses...
// ...
$client = Factory::createWithAccessToken(' ... ');
// build the request...
// ...
try {
    $apiResponse = $client->crm()->deals()->searchApi()->doSearch($publicObjectSearchRequest);
    var_dump($apiRespomse);
} catch (ApiException $e) {
    echo " ... "
}```
edit: solved; I just had to set `curl.cainfo` in `php.ini`. PHP was misconfigured
